<li class="see">Initiate — Things to Post     ← Quick start is here!!!</li>
  <p>Much of modern politics is about division, and trying to score points back when you feel like
the other team has scored a point against you. Finding the right messengers is both powerful
and easy way to short-circuit these divisions. Most of the sports-related messengers are pretty mild: they are standing up for the right to protest, and light on joining the original message. Still, first steps are — by far — the hard ones on crossing political lines. So start here, and then follow up with articles on racism.

<p>The mildest frame — and thus perhaps best for wavering Trump voters — is simply that some of Trump’s past supporters have had enough, and that people whose first loyalty is to sports are unhappy with Trump right now. For liberals this doesn’t feel on-point, but it is likely a powerful place to start, a powerful place to lower the boundaries that get in the way of saners conversations and saner votes. 

<img class="see3" src="images/Messengers.png"/>

  <ul>  
    <li class="see1">Post This! Messengers: Sports -vs- Trump 
<p class="see1">Short version suggestion: if you have friends into sports, post one of these each day, in order, without adding an introduction that changes the voice — not good for arguments, great for atmosphere.</p>

      <ul><li><a href="https://www.si.com/tech-media/2017/09/24/donald-trump-nfl-national-anthem-terry-bradshaw">Terry Bradshaw, modeling stepping gently away from Trump.</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.rawstory.com/2017/09/nbas-steve-kerr-blasts-trump-over-anthem-tantrum-you-know-what-else-is-disrespectful-to-our-flag-racism/">Steve Kerr (NBA) blasts Trump</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/25/cowboys-players-take-a-knee-with-owner-jerry-jones-before-standing-for-anthem/">“Trump Can’t Divide This” on Dallas Cowboys</a> — an amazing opening.</li>
        <li>A long Sports Illustrated article on <a href="A long Sports Illustrated article on Kaepernick as a person that basically calms things down, and creates a nice environment against trolling: https://www.si.com/mmqb/2017/03/30/nfl-colin-kaepernick-free-agent-quarterback-looking-job
  ">Kaepernick as a person</a> that basically calms things down, and creates a nice environment against trolling.</li>
        <li><a href="https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sfgate.com%2Fathletics%2Farticle%2FA-s-Bruce-Maxwell-first-MLB-player-to-kneel-for-12223798.php">Baseball: Great photo of hand on heart, and kneeling.</a>
        <br/><a href="https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sfgate.com%2Fathletics%2Farticle%2FA-s-Bruce-Maxwell-first-MLB-player-to-kneel-for-12223798.php"><img src="./images/BruceMaxwell.png"/></a>
        </li>
        <li>This unfortunately says “Occupy Democrats” but is <a href="https://www.facebook.com/OccupyDemocrats/videos/vb.346937065399354/1713065035453210/?type=2&theater">a sportscaster from Trump’s core demographic of somewhat older white men, a veteran, crushing Trump.</a></li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li class="see">Messenger: Country Music
      <ul><li>
      <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/posteverything/wp/2017/09/29/im-a-white-country-singer-i-still-took-a-knee-after-i-sang-the-national-anthem-at-an-nfl-game/?tid=ss_fb&utm_term=.1068688660b2">Country music takes a knee</a>
      </li></ul>
    </li>

<p>It’s good to be up front: these unity messages are not Kaepernick’s original message, which is getting lost, and if you have an idea that can pull support away from Trump as much as sports teams unifying against him, and at the same time get Kaepernick’s message out, please share it. 

These messengers may
be an opening, a first step, in an environment where usually no progress is made.

these are the opening that is required to make Trump’s divisive distractions backfire, creating space for the real message if anything can. Start with these anti-trolling social media posts to create space, then go back to the voices of the original protest.
</p>
<p>Note that there are three very different voices recommended here. Let messengers and witnesses speak for themselves, without adding your voice. When Trump commits an outrage, when he is trolling, 
speak with, for and as everyone — isolate him, don't let him represent conservatives against the left. When it is time for you to speak, stick to your frame, without saying "no" or 
</p>

