      <p>Many decent conservatives are upset that "their side" is led by Trump. Give them exposure
      to voices "on their side" who see Trump for what he is, for example <a href="https://twitter.com/Evan_McMullin/status/911926608486834177">follow Evan McMullin on twitter.</a> Note: if liberals
take the spotlight from Trump, and instead post civil disagreements with McMullin, that creates
space for conservatives to defend a more decent conservative — possibly the biggest threat to 
Trump and long-term Trump politics.</p>

